# AITBC v0.5.0 Release Plan — Production Infrastructure

## Overview

v0.5.0 follows v0.4.27 and focuses on **infrastructure and state management** — the hardening that can't be done in a single session. v0.4.27 completes the quick wins (JWT migration, CI fixes). v0.5.0 tackles architecture changes.

**Target Date**: Q1 2025 (after v0.4.27)
**Theme**: "Harden the Foundation"
**Success Criteria**: All services are stateful, observable, and production-deployable.

## Overall Status

| Priority | Area | Status | Notes |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| **P0** | DB/Redis Backing for Mock State | ✅ Complete | RedisStateManager with in-memory fallback |
| **P1** | Systemd Hardening | ✅ Complete | Security directives complete, user migration tooling ready |
| **P1** | Observability Standardization | ✅ Complete | Coordinator API, blockchain-node, marketplace JSON logging enabled |
| **P1** | Secret Management | ✅ Complete | Audit/fixes complete, rotation runbook documented |
| **P1** | Performance Baseline | ✅ Complete | Infrastructure, CI, measurements complete |
| **P2** | CI/CD Hardening | ✅ Complete | Coverage gates, flaky-test detection, separate jobs |
| **P2** | Security Depth | ✅ Complete | Network policy documented, secret rotation runbook |
| **P2** | Code Quality | ✅ Complete | Type coverage, integration tests added |
| **P2** | Observability Depth | ✅ Complete | SLOs defined, log schema tests added |

**Summary**: All P0 and P1 tasks complete. P2 tasks (CI/CD hardening, security depth, code quality, observability depth) also completed.

